Clear- calm- cool.  Still some algae bloom.
Lake very green in some places.

Very slight breeze- overcast- very light precipitation- 60 degrees F.
Partly cloudy/Sunny- 10-15 mph NW-W breeze- slight chop on water. Only 1 other boat on the lake. One loon spotted.
Sky was clear with a S-SW breeze 10-15 mph- 78 degrees F.
Mostly sunny- slight NW breeze- loons with 2 young spotted on lake. Lake level about normal for this time of year.
Lake is like a mirror.  Clear skies- calm- 75 degrees F.- two musky fishermen nearby. After secchi reading- a jet ski spooked 2 loons with young near center of lake. Man did they raise a ruckus!

column1: Shortly thereafter- a 40-50 inch musky surfaced right next to my pontoon. Quite a morning!
wind speed aprox. 2 mph from sw

column2: Clear sky- SSE wind 10-15 mph- 76 degrees F. Clear sky- SSE wind 10-15 mph- 76 degrees F.
Partly Cloudy- Slight Northerly breeze- slight algae bloom- 60 degrees F.

Slight variable breeze- 62 degrees F.- partly cloudy. Water looks good. When I stopped the pontoon to do the secchi a very large loon startled me when it surfaced about 5 feet from the boat. I had no idea it was even anywhere near the area until it popped up. It gave me a long look and then swam away. Should have had the camera!
Clear skies- slight NE breeze. Temperature 82 degrees F. One Loon close by.
Clear sky- slight easterly breeze- temperature 68 degrees F. Pair of Loons near sampling site.
FOUND A PIECE OF EURASIAN WATER MILFOIL
Clear to partly cloudy skies. Air temp. 70 degrees F.Southerly breeze 5-10.

column1: Pair of loons 50 yards to south.

column2: Air temp 65 degrees F.- clear to partly cloudy- NW wind at about 10 mph. Can hear loon in the distance.
Air temp 85 degrees F.- South wind at 10-15 mph. Sky partly cloudy. No loons today.
Very slight NE breeze. Air temp 60 degrees F.. Sky clear. We've had 4 inches of rain in the last few days.
Sky partly cloudy. Air temp 75 degrees F. Light SW breeze. Slight algae bloom evident. Adult loon with one youngster about 50 feet from boat. Appears to be teaching the kid how to dive- what a sight!

Clear sky- NNW breeze 5 mph. Water appears gr/br in color. Lake level has been higher than usual. Huge beaver dam discovered along the Amnicon River south of the lake- which explains unusual high water levels for this time of year. Lake district working with trapper to alleviate problem.
Sky mostly clear; wind Westerly at 5-10 mph; Air temp 78 degrees F.; water temp at 10 inches below surface 64 degrees F.
Sky clear to partly cloudy- air temp. 65 degree F.- calm- no wind at all.
Sky mostly cloudy- air temp 75 degrees F.-  SSE wind about 5-10 mph.

column1: We have received 4.75 inches of rain since June 5 reading.

column2: Clear sky- calm- air temp. 78 degrees F.
Clear sky- vary slight variable breeze- air temp. 85 degrees F.
Clear sky- WSW breeze 5-10 mph. air temp 70 degrees F.
Partly cloudy sky- slight northerly breeze. Air temp 55 degrees F.
Wind 5 mph N lake is mixing
Clear sky- calm. Air temp 48 degrees F.. Water temp at 1 ft- 50 degrees F.
Clear sky- wind variable at 5-10 mph. Air temp. 54 degrees F.- water temp at 1 ft. 49 degrees F.
Mostly cloudy- air temp 52 degrees F.- wind ENE at 10-15 mph. Encountered 1 large loon along the north shore of the lake.
Overcast- air temp 54 degrees F.- NW wind at 3-5. Sighted 1 loon NE of public landing.
Sky mostly clear- air temp 85 degrees F.- wind WSW 5-15 mph. Sure have had our share of rain. Had another 2.25 inches on July 1.
Clear sky- air temp 79 degrees F.- wind light + variable. Water level still high.  Spotted 1 pontoon- 1 runabout- 1 sailboat and 1 jet ski. Oh - and 1 lone Canada Goose NE of Tomahawk Island.

Clear sky- air temp 80 degrees F. Westerly wind at 5-10 mph. Water level extremely high and rising fast. My rain gauge showed 4.25 inches of rain- some neighbors had 5.5 inches and others a short distance away from the lake had close to 8 inches. Had to use knee boots to get to the pontoon.

Haven't been able to get to the pontoon since the 3rd. My depth finder reads 34 feet over the deep hole (which is normally 31 feet. The three culverts at the south end of the lake that normally empty into the Amnicon River ran backwards for the better part of a week. The culverts are about 36" in diameter and were filled to the top. There were several roads washed out in the area. The water level at Lyman Lake east of Amnicon reportedly rose 4 feet during this siege. Mother Nature.....gotta love her!

Sky partly cloudy- air temp 64 degrees F. water temp at 10 inches is 78 degrees F. Wind WSW at 5-10 mph. Slight algae bloom in progress causing water to appear greenish/brown. Water has finally receded to a more normal level. Many people had to track down sections of their docks etc. after the flood.
Partly cloudy- West wind at 10-15 mph- air temperature 65 degrees F. 1 Bald eagle sighted over lake. 1 young loon sighted near north shore of lake.
Clear sky- wind N/NE @ 5-15- air temperature 40 degrees F.- water temp @ 12'' below surface 50 degrees F. 1 adult loon spotted near public landing.
Partly cloudy- south wind at 10-15 mph. Air temperature 84 degrees F.
Clear sky- south wind at 10-20 mph. air temperature 81 degrees F. Water temp at 1 ft. depth 78 degrees F.
Partly cloudy sky- air temperature 75 degrees F. Water has a definite green tint.
Clear sky- slight breeze less than 10 mph. Water temperature at 1 foot depth 71 degrees F.
Clear sky northerly breeze 5 mph- air temperature 57 degrees F.- water temperature at 1 ft. depth 65 degrees F.
Clear sky- light NE breeze. Air temperature 67 degrees F.- water temperature at 1 ft. 55 degrees F.
Overcast- strong SE wind- some whitecaps. Air temperature 50 degrees F.- water temperature at 1 ft. 44 degrees F.
Clear sky- calm. Air temperature 50 degrees F.- water temperature at 1 ft. depth 45 degrees F. Loon calling in the distance.
Partly cloudy- wind west at 10-15 mph- air temperature 88 degrees F.- water temp at 1 ft. 77 degrees F.
Partly cloudy- slight WSW breeze- Air temperature 78 degrees F.
Clear sky- WSW wind at 10-15 mph- air temperature 86 degrees F.
Cold North wind @ 5-10 mph- partly cloudy- air temperature 60 degrees F. (rude awakening after many hot and humid days). One bald eagle soaring over SE end of lake.
Mostly cloudy- wind WSW @ 5-10- air temp 73 degrees F.
Clear- sunny- air temp 62 degrees F. Wind SE @ 5 mph. One loon spotted near north shore.
Clear sky- north wind @ 5-10 mph- air temp. 65 degrees F.

Beautiful day- sunny w/high cirrus clouds- light wind 5-10 mph. Air temperature 64 degrees F.- water temp at 1 ft. depth 55 degrees F. 2.75" of rain in past 2 weeks. One loon sighted near Twin Pine Island.
Clear sky- calm wind- air temperature 71 degrees F.. Water temp at 1 ft. depth 72 degrees F.
Clear sky- slight NNW breeze- air temperature 90 degrees F.. Water temperature at 1 ft. depth 79 degrees F. No algae bloom apparent. Lke area has received 3.5" rain in past 2 weeks.
Slight overcast- light South wind- nearly calm. Air temp. 77 degrees F. 1 loon sighted near Twin Pine Island.
Clear sky- wind NNE at 10-15 mph- Air temp. 57 degrees F. Slight algae bloom dor last 2 weeks.
Gorgeous day! Air temp 80 degrees F.- south wind at 10-15 mph- clear sky.

column1: One young loon spotted between Finn Point and Twin Pine Island.

column2: Clear to partly cloudy- WSW wind 10-15 mph. Two loons spotted near northeast shore of Twin Pine Island.
Mostly cloudy- light ENE wind- air temp. 55 degrees F.
Weather was calm with clear sky and air temperature of 70 degrees F. Surface water @ 1 ft. was 63 degrees F.

Cloudy sky- wind light/variable. Air Temp 55 degrees F. Two loons performing what appeared to be a mating ritual on the north end of the lake. They even buzzed my pontoon a few times as close as 25-30 feet. What a show they put on! Later I spotted a single loon Tomahawk Island.
Overcast- nearly calm wind- air temp 56 degrees F. One loon sighted north of Tomahawk Island. One Bald Eagle circling overhead.
Partly Cloudy- air temp. 73 degrees F. Westerly wind 15 gusting to 25.
Partly cloudy sky- calm wind- air temp 73 degrees F- water temp at 1 ft.- 74 degrees F. Three loons sighted near the deep hole- one adult 2 young.
Clear sky- wind nearly calm- air temp. 83 degrees F. Several fishermen in boats- a few pontoons  cruising- one water skier sighted.
Partly Cloudy sky- air temp. 75 degrees F.- southerly wind 10-15 mph.
Clear sky- very slight SW breeze.
Cloudy- 72 degrees F.- light southerly wind.
Partly Cloudy- 72 degrees F.- Southerly wind 5-10 mph.
One loon sighted near north shore of lake.
Partly to mostly cloudy- calm- air temp 47 degrees F.- surface water temp at 1 ft. 51 degrees F.
Mostly clear sky- wind S/SW 5-15- air temp 74 degrees F.- water temp at 1 foot 73 degrees F. One loon with 2 chicks on north end of lake.
Clear sky- variable wind at 5 mph- air temperature 77 degrees F. Loon sighted  near eastern shore.
Clear sky- slight NE breeze- air temp. 65 degrees F.
Light overcast- calm wind. Slight green tinge to surface water.
Clear sky wind 5-10 mph SE. Air temp 70 degrees F. Water temp at 1 ft. 67 degrees F. Bald Eagle sighted atop dead pine tree on Twin Pine Island.
Clear sky- calm- air temp 52 degrees F. Beautiful morning but lake is up and dirty due to at least 3 inches of rain since 10/1.
Air temp. 70 degrees- mostly cloudy sky- lake level still receding from June 16 flood- now showing 1 ft. above 31' datum at 32'. One Loon sighted on north side of lake.
70 degrees air temp- partly cloudy sky- wind NW at 5-10. One Loon sighted near deep hole.
Partly sunny- air temperature 70 degrees F.- south wind 10-15. Air temp. 70 degrees F.- wind So. at 10-15- Partly sunny.
One Loon sighted 200 ft. southeast of public landing.
Partly cloudy- air temp 70 degrees F. Wind WSW at 5-15.
